WEBVTT

1
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:14,600
Hello.

2
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:18,229
My name's Forrest. Forrest Gump.

3
00:03:23,777 --> 00:03:25,820
Do you want a chocolate?

4
00:03:28,406 --> 00:03:31,826
I could eat about
a million and a half of these.

5
00:03:32,994 --> 00:03:38,207
My mama always said
life was like a box of chocolates.

6
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:43,087
You never know what you're gonna get.

7
00:03:50,303 --> 00:03:52,847
Those must be comfortable shoes.

8
00:03:54,224 --> 00:03:58,894
I'll bet you could walk all day
in shoes like that and not feel a thing.

9
00:04:01,106 --> 00:04:03,566
I wish I had shoes like that.

10
00:04:04,234 --> 00:04:05,776
My feet hurt.

11
00:04:06,987 --> 00:04:08,654
Mama always said there's an awful lot

12
00:04:08,738 --> 00:04:11,949
you could tell about a person
by their shoes:

13
00:04:13,076 --> 00:04:16,036
Where they're going,
where they've been.

14
00:04:23,295 --> 00:04:25,337
I've worn lots of shoes.

15
00:04:28,465 --> 00:04:33,261
I bet if I think about it real hard,
I could remember my first pair of shoes.

16
00:04:36,182 --> 00:04:38,808
Mama said they'd take me anywhere.

17
00:04:39,602 --> 00:04:42,228
She said they was my magic shoes.

18
00:04:42,313 --> 00:04:45,481
All right, Forrest,
you can open your eyes now.

19
00:04:52,781 --> 00:04:55,241
Let's take a little walk around.

20
00:05:02,041 --> 00:05:03,833
How do those feel?

21
00:05:06,795 --> 00:05:08,963
His legs are strong, Mrs. Gump,

22
00:05:09,048 --> 00:05:11,549
as strong as I've ever seen,

23
00:05:11,634 --> 00:05:15,011
but his back is as crooked
as a politician.

24
00:05:16,305 --> 00:05:19,390
But we're gonna straighten him right up,
now, aren't we, Forrest?

25
00:05:19,475 --> 00:05:20,600
Forrest!

26
00:05:22,102 --> 00:05:23,311
Now, when I was a baby,

27
00:05:23,395 --> 00:05:26,231
Mama named me after
the great Civil War hero,

28
00:05:26,315 --> 00:05:28,733
General Nathan Bedford Forrest.

29
00:05:28,817 --> 00:05:31,027
She said we was related to him
in some way.

30
00:05:31,111 --> 00:05:32,487
And what he did was,

31
00:05:32,571 --> 00:05:36,824
he started up this club called
the Ku Klux Klan.

32
00:05:36,909 --> 00:05:40,245
They'd all dress up in their robes
and their bed sheets

33
00:05:40,329 --> 00:05:44,666
and act like a bunch of ghosts
or spooks or something.

34
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:48,628
They'd even put bed sheets
on their horses and ride around.

35
00:05:48,712 --> 00:05:51,756
And anyway, that's how I got my name,

36
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,258
Forrest Gump.

37
00:05:53,342 --> 00:05:55,093
Mama said that the "Forrest" part

38
00:05:55,177 --> 00:05:58,721
was to remind me that sometimes
we all do things that,

39
00:05:58,806 --> 00:06:01,599
well, just don't make no sense.

40
00:06:07,273 --> 00:06:10,775
Okay... Get it, get it...

41
00:06:10,859 --> 00:06:13,820
Wait, is it this way? Hold on.

42
00:06:14,738 --> 00:06:16,239
All right...

43
00:06:16,824 --> 00:06:18,491
What are you all staring at?

44
00:06:18,575 --> 00:06:23,037
Haven't you ever seen a little boy
with braces on his legs before?

45
00:06:24,581 --> 00:06:28,293
Don't ever let anybody tell you
they're better than you, Forrest.

46
00:06:28,377 --> 00:06:30,962
If God intended
everybody to be the same,

47
00:06:31,046 --> 00:06:33,172
he'd have given us all braces
on our legs.

48
00:06:33,257 --> 00:06:37,051
Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.

49
00:06:38,512 --> 00:06:42,015
We lived about a quarter mile
off Route 17,

50
00:06:42,099 --> 00:06:45,143
about a half mile from
the town of Greenbow, Alabama.

51
00:06:45,227 --> 00:06:47,979
That's in the county of Greenbow.

52
00:06:48,063 --> 00:06:52,483
Our house had been in Mama's family
since her grandpa's grandpa's grandpa

53
00:06:52,568 --> 00:06:54,485
had come across the ocean
about 1,000 years ago,

54
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:56,486
something like that.

55
00:06:56,571 --> 00:06:59,281
Since it was just me and Mama
and we had all these empty rooms,

56
00:06:59,365 --> 00:07:02,117
Mama decided to let those rooms out,

57
00:07:02,201 --> 00:07:04,161
mostly to people passing through,

58
00:07:04,245 --> 00:07:08,206
like from, oh, Mobile,
Montgomery, places like that.

59
00:07:08,291 --> 00:07:11,001
That's how me and Mama got money.

60
00:07:11,085 --> 00:07:13,837
Mama was a real smart lady.

61
00:07:13,921 --> 00:07:18,925
Remember what I told you, Forrest.
You're no different than anybody else is.

62
00:07:21,429 --> 00:07:23,805
Did you hear what I said, Forrest?

63
00:07:23,890 --> 00:07:28,060
You're the same as everybody else.
You are no different.

64
00:07:28,561 --> 00:07:33,023
Your boy's different, Mrs. Gump.

65
00:07:33,107 --> 00:07:35,317
Now, his IQ is 75.

66
00:07:36,110 --> 00:07:39,237
Well, we're all different, Mr. Hancock.

67
00:07:42,825 --> 00:07:44,868
She wanted me to have
the finest education,

68
00:07:44,952 --> 00:07:48,872
so she took me to
the Greenbow County Central School.

69
00:07:48,956 --> 00:07:51,208
I met the principal and all.

70
00:07:51,709 --> 00:07:54,586
I want to show you something,
Mrs. Gump.

71
00:07:55,046 --> 00:07:57,923
Now, this is normal.

72
00:07:58,424 --> 00:08:01,718
Forrest is right here.

73
00:08:02,553 --> 00:08:08,100
The state requires a minimum IQ of
80 to attend public school, Mrs. Gump.

74
00:08:08,601 --> 00:08:11,478
He's gonna have to go
to a special school.

75
00:08:11,562 --> 00:08:13,688
Now, he'll be just fine.

76
00:08:14,482 --> 00:08:16,566
What does "normal" mean, anyway?

77
00:08:16,651 --> 00:08:20,028
He might be a bit on the slow side,

78
00:08:21,155 --> 00:08:22,906
but my boy Forrest is gonna get

79
00:08:22,990 --> 00:08:25,534
the same opportunities
as everyone else.

80
00:08:25,618 --> 00:08:29,413
He's not going to some special school
to learn how to re-tread tires.

81
00:08:29,497 --> 00:08:32,666
We're talking about
five little points here.

82
00:08:34,377 --> 00:08:37,003
There must be something can be done.

83
00:08:38,589 --> 00:08:41,049
We're a progressive school system.

84
00:08:41,884 --> 00:08:44,803
We don't want to see anybody
left behind.

85
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:49,141
Is there a Mr. Gump, Mrs. Gump?

86
00:08:52,395 --> 00:08:54,271
He's on vacation.

87
00:09:11,747 --> 00:09:15,542
Well, your mama sure does care
about your schooling, son.

88
00:09:21,048 --> 00:09:23,507
You don't say much, do you?

89
00:09:35,020 --> 00:09:36,979
"Finally, he had to try.

90
00:09:37,063 --> 00:09:39,023
"It looked easy, but,

91
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:42,568
"oh, what happened.

92
00:09:42,652 --> 00:09:45,654
- "First, there..."
- Mama, what's "vacation" mean?

93
00:09:46,198 --> 00:09:48,782
- Vacation?
- Where Daddy went.

94
00:09:51,411 --> 00:09:54,121
Vacation's when you go somewhere

95
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:58,834
and you don't ever come back.

96
00:10:03,173 --> 00:10:06,967
Anyway, I guess you could say
me and Mama was on our own.

97
00:10:08,178 --> 00:10:11,805
But we didn't mind.
Our house was never empty.

98
00:10:11,890 --> 00:10:14,475
There was always folks
coming and going.

99
00:10:14,559 --> 00:10:15,643
Supper.

100
00:10:15,727 --> 00:10:19,146
- It's supper, everyone. Forrest...
- My, my. That sure looks special.

101
00:10:19,231 --> 00:10:21,774
Sometimes we had
so many people staying with us

102
00:10:21,858 --> 00:10:24,527
that every room
was filled with travelers.

103
00:10:24,611 --> 00:10:28,239
You know, folks living out
of their suitcases

104
00:10:28,323 --> 00:10:31,283
and hat cases and sample cases.

105
00:10:31,368 --> 00:10:34,787
Forrest Gump, it's suppertime!
Forrest...

106
00:10:34,871 --> 00:10:37,414
One time, a young man
was staying with us,

107
00:10:37,499 --> 00:10:41,126
and he had him a guitar case.

108
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:59,103
Forrest! I told you not to bother
this nice young man.

109
00:10:59,187 --> 00:11:00,521
Oh, no, that's all right, ma'am.

110
00:11:00,605 --> 00:11:03,440
I was just showing him a thing or two
on the guitar here.

111
00:11:03,525 --> 00:11:06,485
All right, but your supper's ready
if y'all want to eat.

112
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:09,530
Yeah, that sounds good.
Thank you, ma'am.

113
00:11:10,198 --> 00:11:13,784
Say, man, show me that crazy
little walk you just did there.

114
00:11:13,868 --> 00:11:15,744
Slow it down some.

115
00:11:17,872 --> 00:11:19,790
I liked that guitar.

116
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:22,209
It sounded good.

117
00:11:24,004 --> 00:11:28,173
I started moving around to the music,

118
00:11:28,258 --> 00:11:30,092
swinging my hips.

119
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:35,222
This one night,
me and Mama was out shopping,

120
00:11:35,307 --> 00:11:38,309
and we walked right by
Benson's furniture and appliance store,

121
00:11:38,393 --> 00:11:39,977
and guess what?

122
00:11:52,323 --> 00:11:55,158
This is not for children's eyes.

123
00:11:57,703 --> 00:11:59,495
Some years later,
that handsome young man

124
00:11:59,580 --> 00:12:02,123
who they called "The King,"

125
00:12:02,207 --> 00:12:04,542
well, he'd sung too many songs,

126
00:12:05,210 --> 00:12:07,754
had himself a heart attack,
or something.

127
00:12:08,839 --> 00:12:11,007
Must be hard being a king.

128
00:12:15,304 --> 00:12:18,139
You know, it's funny how you remember
some things, but some things you can't.

129
00:12:18,891 --> 00:12:22,769
- You do your very best now, Forrest.
- I sure will, Mama.

130
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:29,067
I remember the bus ride
on the first day of school very well.

131
00:12:32,613 --> 00:12:34,322
Are you coming along?

132
00:12:34,406 --> 00:12:37,909
Mama said not to be taking
rides from strangers.

133
00:12:37,993 --> 00:12:40,161
This is the bus to school.

134
00:12:43,123 --> 00:12:45,375
I'm Forrest. Forrest Gump.

135
00:12:46,335 --> 00:12:50,338
- I'm Dorothy Harris.
- Well, now we ain't strangers anymore.

136
00:13:03,352 --> 00:13:05,144
This seat's taken.

137
00:13:07,606 --> 00:13:09,107
It's taken!

138
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:18,866
You can't sit here.

139
00:13:21,036 --> 00:13:24,455
You know, it's funny what
a young man recollects,

140
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:26,916
'cause I don't remember being born.

141
00:13:28,544 --> 00:13:30,712
I don't recall what I got
for my first Christmas,

142
00:13:30,796 --> 00:13:33,881
and I don't know when I went
on my first outdoor picnic.

143
00:13:33,966 --> 00:13:38,678
But I do remember the first time I heard

144
00:13:38,762 --> 00:13:41,597
the sweetest voice in the wide world.

145
00:13:42,099 --> 00:13:44,475
You can sit here if you want.

146
00:13:47,396 --> 00:13:51,274
I had never seen anything
so beautiful in my life.

147
00:13:51,984 --> 00:13:54,068
She was like an angel.

148
00:13:54,153 --> 00:13:57,071
Well, are you gonna sit down,
or aren't you?

149
00:14:02,035 --> 00:14:03,828
What's wrong with your legs?

150
00:14:03,912 --> 00:14:08,166
Nothing at all, thank you.
My legs are just fine and dandy.

151
00:14:09,084 --> 00:14:11,252
I just sat next to her on that bus

152
00:14:11,336 --> 00:14:13,421
and had a conversation
all the way to school.

153
00:14:13,505 --> 00:14:16,215
...my back's crooked like
a question mark.

154
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:17,467
These are going to make me...

155
00:14:17,551 --> 00:14:22,304
And next to Mama, no one ever
talked to me or asked me questions.

156
00:14:22,847 --> 00:14:24,806
Are you stupid or something?

157
00:14:24,891 --> 00:14:27,893
Mama says, "Stupid is as stupid does."

158
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:33,190
- I'm Jenny.
- I'm Forrest. Forrest Gump.

159
00:14:33,858 --> 00:14:35,692
From that day on,
we was always together.

160
00:14:35,777 --> 00:14:38,612
Jenny and me was like
peas and carrots.

161
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,825
She taught me how to climb.

162
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:46,620
Come on, Forrest, you can do it.

163
00:14:46,704 --> 00:14:49,331
I showed her how to dangle.

164
00:14:49,415 --> 00:14:51,458
"...a good little monkey and..."

165
00:14:51,542 --> 00:14:56,463
She helped me learn how to read,
and I showed her how to swing.

166
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:02,552
Sometimes we'd just sit out
and wait for the stars.

167
00:15:02,637 --> 00:15:07,557
- Mama's gonna worry about me.
- Just stay a little longer.

168
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:12,562
For some reason,
Jenny didn't never want to go home.

169
00:15:12,647 --> 00:15:14,731
Okay, Jenny, I'll stay.

170
00:15:15,566 --> 00:15:18,318
She was my most special friend.

171
00:15:21,739 --> 00:15:23,406
My only friend.

172
00:15:27,203 --> 00:15:30,997
Now, my mama always told me that
miracles happen every day.

173
00:15:31,082 --> 00:15:33,458
Some people don't think so, but they do.

174
00:15:36,504 --> 00:15:38,088
Hey, dummy!

175
00:15:39,048 --> 00:15:41,132
Are you retarded, or just plain stupid?

176
00:15:41,217 --> 00:15:44,719
- "Look, I'm Forrest Gimp."
- Just run away, Forrest.

177
00:15:46,055 --> 00:15:49,140
Run, Forrest! Run away! Hurry!

178
00:15:49,225 --> 00:15:52,477
- Get the bikes!
- Hurry up! Let's get him!

179
00:15:52,562 --> 00:15:55,105
- Come on!
- Look out, dummy, here we come!

180
00:15:55,189 --> 00:15:57,023
We're gonna get you!

181
00:15:57,984 --> 00:16:01,736
Run, Forrest, run! Run, Forrest!

182
00:16:03,447 --> 00:16:05,365
Come back here, you!

183
00:16:19,005 --> 00:16:21,464
Run, Forrest!

184
00:16:21,549 --> 00:16:22,966
Run!

185
00:16:54,164 --> 00:16:57,041
Now, you wouldn't believe it
if I told you,

186
00:16:58,168 --> 00:17:00,669
but I can run like the wind blows.

187
00:17:03,924 --> 00:17:07,009
From that day on,
if I was going somewhere,

188
00:17:07,844 --> 00:17:09,136
I was running!

189
00:17:09,220 --> 00:17:11,597
He's getting away! Stop him!

190
00:17:43,046 --> 00:17:46,048
That boy sure is a running fool.

191
00:17:50,261 --> 00:17:51,637
Now, remember how I told you that

192
00:17:51,721 --> 00:17:54,640
Jenny never seemed
to want to go home?

193
00:17:54,724 --> 00:17:57,810
Well, she lived in a house
that was as old as Alabama.

194
00:17:57,894 --> 00:18:00,062
Her mama had gone up to heaven
when she was five,

195
00:18:00,146 --> 00:18:03,482
and her daddy was
some kind of a farmer.

196
00:18:05,318 --> 00:18:06,360
Jenny?

197
00:18:06,444 --> 00:18:08,612
He was a very loving man.

198
00:18:09,072 --> 00:18:13,325
He was always kissing and touching
her and her sisters.

199
00:18:15,078 --> 00:18:19,498
And then this one time,
Jenny wasn't on the bus to go to school.

200
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:23,544
Jenny, why didn't you come
to school today?

201
00:18:23,628 --> 00:18:25,671
Daddy's taking a nap.

202
00:18:25,755 --> 00:18:27,464
- Jenny!
- Come on!

203
00:18:28,925 --> 00:18:31,468
Jenny, where'd you run to?

204
00:18:32,804 --> 00:18:35,472
You'd better get back here, girl!

205
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:38,600
Where you at?

206
00:18:41,980 --> 00:18:45,274
Jenny! Jenny! Where you at?

207
00:18:48,278 --> 00:18:49,611
Jenny!

208
00:18:49,696 --> 00:18:52,656
Pray with me, Forrest. Pray with me.

209
00:18:52,782 --> 00:18:53,907
Jenny!

210
00:18:53,992 --> 00:18:57,202
Dear God, make me a bird
so I can fly far,

211
00:18:57,287 --> 00:18:59,038
far, far away from here.

212
00:18:59,122 --> 00:19:02,791
Dear God, make me a bird
so I can fly far,

213
00:19:02,876 --> 00:19:04,001
far, far away from here.

214
00:19:04,127 --> 00:19:07,171
Mama always said
that God is mysterious.

215
00:19:07,297 --> 00:19:08,422
Jenny!

216
00:19:08,506 --> 00:19:10,841
He didn't turn Jenny into a bird that day.

217
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:12,051
You'd better get back here!

218
00:19:12,135 --> 00:19:13,635
Instead,

219
00:19:14,304 --> 00:19:18,848
he had the police say Jenny didn't
have to stay in that house no more.

220
00:19:19,308 --> 00:19:23,019
She went to live with her grandma
just over on Creekmore Avenue,

221
00:19:23,145 --> 00:19:26,314
which made me happy,
'cause she was so close.

222
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:33,946
Some nights, Jenny would sneak out
and come on over to my house,

223
00:19:34,031 --> 00:19:37,158
just 'cause she said she was scared.

224
00:19:37,242 --> 00:19:39,702
Scared of what, I don't know,

225
00:19:39,828 --> 00:19:43,039
but I think it was her grandma's dog.

226
00:19:43,165 --> 00:19:44,916
He was a mean dog.

227
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:48,377
Anyway, Jenny and me was best friends

228
00:19:48,462 --> 00:19:49,754
all the way up through high school.

229
00:19:51,715 --> 00:19:53,758
- Hey, stupid!
- Quit it!

230
00:19:54,885 --> 00:19:57,178
- Run, Forrest, run!
- Hey,

231
00:19:57,888 --> 00:19:59,347
did you hear me, stupid?

232
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:00,640
- Run, Forrest!
- Come on, get in the truck!

233
00:20:00,724 --> 00:20:02,850
Get in the truck! Let's move it!

234
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:05,686
Come on, he's getting away! Move it!

235
00:20:05,771 --> 00:20:07,939
Run, Forrest! Run!

236
00:20:08,023 --> 00:20:11,567
- You better be running, stupid!
- Come on, dummy!

237
00:20:13,529 --> 00:20:17,031
- Haul ass, dummy!
- Yeah, you better get running!

238
00:20:20,035 --> 00:20:21,702
Jack rabbit!

239
00:20:30,129 --> 00:20:31,379
Yeah!

240
00:20:32,214 --> 00:20:34,382
Go! Go! Go!

241
00:20:36,093 --> 00:20:37,718
Run, Forrest!

242
00:20:40,722 --> 00:20:44,308
Now, it used to be,
I ran to get where I was going,

243
00:20:45,894 --> 00:20:48,396
I never thought it would
take me anywhere.

244
00:21:17,426 --> 00:21:21,596
- Who in the hell is that?
- That there is Forrest Gump, Coach.

245
00:21:22,598 --> 00:21:24,432
Just a local idiot.

246
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:28,603
And can you believe it?
I got to go to college, too.

247
00:21:35,194 --> 00:21:37,820
Forrest! Forrest! Run!

248
00:21:37,946 --> 00:21:39,530
- Okay!
- Run!

