00:39:09,155 --> 00:39:13,617
Forrest, you stay away from me, okay?
You just stay away from me, please.

494
00:39:13,701 --> 00:39:14,993
Can I have a ride?

495
00:39:15,078 --> 00:39:16,620
- Where you going?
- I don't care.

496
00:39:16,704 --> 00:39:18,080
Get in the truck.

497
00:39:18,164 --> 00:39:19,998
So, bye-bye, Jenny.

498
00:39:22,502 --> 00:39:24,836
They sending me to Vietnam.

499
00:39:27,590 --> 00:39:30,008
It's this whole other country.

500
00:39:32,512 --> 00:39:34,513
Just hang on a minute.

501
00:39:35,932 --> 00:39:38,976
Listen, you promise me
something, okay?

502
00:39:39,060 --> 00:39:42,396
Just, if you're ever in trouble,
don't try to be brave. You just run, okay?

503
00:39:42,522 --> 00:39:44,106
Just run away.

504
00:39:45,358 --> 00:39:46,692
Okay.

505
00:39:51,572 --> 00:39:52,906
Jenny.

506
00:39:54,784 --> 00:39:57,077
I'll write you all the time.

507
00:40:06,212 --> 00:40:09,214
And just like that, she was gone.

508
00:40:25,315 --> 00:40:28,650
You come back safe to me,
do you hear?

509
00:41:11,944 --> 00:41:15,906
Now, they told us that Vietnam
was gonna be very different

510
00:41:15,990 --> 00:41:18,867
from the United States of America.

511
00:41:18,951 --> 00:41:23,997
And except for all the beer cans
and the barbecue, it was.

512
00:41:34,132 --> 00:41:37,218
Hey, I bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

513
00:41:37,302 --> 00:41:40,471
They tell me these Vietnams
is good shrimpers.

514
00:41:40,555 --> 00:41:44,100
You know, after we win this war,
and we take over everything,

515
00:41:44,184 --> 00:41:45,393
we can get American shrimpers

516
00:41:45,477 --> 00:41:47,228
to come out here
and shrimp these waters.

517
00:41:47,312 --> 00:41:48,854
We'll just shrimp all the time, man.

518
00:41:48,980 --> 00:41:52,149
So much shrimp, why,
you wouldn't believe it.

519
00:41:52,818 --> 00:41:54,735
You must be my FNGs.

520
00:41:54,820 --> 00:41:56,070
- Morning, sir!
- Morning, sir!

521
00:41:56,154 --> 00:41:58,781
Get your hands down! Do not salute me.

522
00:41:58,865 --> 00:42:00,991
There's goddamn snipers
all around this area

523
00:42:01,076 --> 00:42:03,911
who would love to grease an officer.

524
00:42:03,995 --> 00:42:07,498
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fourth Platoon.

525
00:42:08,375 --> 00:42:10,793
What's wrong with your lip?

526
00:42:10,877 --> 00:42:13,254
I was born with big gums, sir.

527
00:42:13,338 --> 00:42:18,050
Yeah, well, you better tuck that in.
Gonna get that caught on a trip wire.

528
00:42:19,219 --> 00:42:20,594
Where you boys from in the world?

529
00:42:20,679 --> 00:42:23,055
- Alabama, sir!
- Alabama, sir!

530
00:42:23,765 --> 00:42:25,266
You twins?

531
00:42:27,352 --> 00:42:29,770
No, we are not relations, sir.

532
00:42:32,023 --> 00:42:34,942
Look, it's pretty basic here.

533
00:42:35,735 --> 00:42:38,195
If you stick with me
and learn from the guys

534
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:40,948
who've been in country a while,
you'll be all right.

535
00:42:41,032 --> 00:42:42,950
There is one item of GI gear

536
00:42:43,034 --> 00:42:47,204
that can be the difference between
a live grunt and a dead grunt.

537
00:42:47,539 --> 00:42:50,708
Socks. Cushion sole, OD green.

538
00:42:50,792 --> 00:42:52,084
Try and keep your feet dry.

539
00:42:52,210 --> 00:42:53,627
When we're out humping,
I want you boys to remember

540
00:42:53,712 --> 00:42:56,172
to change your socks
whenever we stop.

541
00:42:56,256 --> 00:42:59,216
The Mekong will eat a grunt's feet
right off his legs.

542
00:42:59,301 --> 00:43:01,594
Sergeant Sims, God damn it,

543
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:03,137
where is that sling rope
I told you to order?

544
00:43:03,221 --> 00:43:05,139
I put in the requisitions at Battalion.

545
00:43:05,223 --> 00:43:07,224
Yeah, yeah, yeah, well,
you call those sons of bitches again...

546
00:43:07,309 --> 00:43:12,229
Lieutenant Dan sure knew his stuff.
I felt real lucky he was my lieutenant.

547
00:43:12,981 --> 00:43:16,442
He was from a long,
great military tradition.

548
00:43:16,651 --> 00:43:19,737
Somebody in his family
had fought and died

549
00:43:20,739 --> 00:43:24,992
in every single American war.

550
00:43:25,911 --> 00:43:27,912
- God damn it, kick some ass!
- I'm on it, Lieutenant.

551
00:43:27,996 --> 00:43:29,121
Get on it!

552
00:43:29,247 --> 00:43:32,583
I guess you could say he had
a lot to live up to.

553
00:43:34,294 --> 00:43:39,131
So, you boys are from Arkansas, huh?
Well, I've been through there.

554
00:43:39,257 --> 00:43:41,425
Little Rock's a fine town.

555
00:43:42,093 --> 00:43:45,679
Now, go shake down your gear,
see the platoon sergeant,

556
00:43:45,764 --> 00:43:48,224
draw what you need for the field.

557
00:43:48,308 --> 00:43:52,269
If you boys are hungry,
we got steaks burning right over here.

558
00:43:52,354 --> 00:43:55,230
Two standing orders in this platoon:

559
00:43:55,314 --> 00:43:57,982
One, take good care of your feet,

560
00:43:58,108 --> 00:44:03,154
two, try not to do anything stupid,
like getting yourself killed.

561
00:44:09,620 --> 00:44:11,704
I sure hope I don't let him down.

562
00:44:23,300 --> 00:44:28,221
I got to see a lot of the countryside.
We would take these real long walks.

563
00:44:36,689 --> 00:44:40,817
And we were always looking
for this guy named Charlie.

564
00:44:48,659 --> 00:44:50,910
- Hold it up!
- Hold up, boys!

565
00:44:53,747 --> 00:44:56,082
It wasn't always fun.

566
00:44:56,166 --> 00:45:00,461
Lieutenant Dan was always getting
these funny feelings about a rock,

567
00:45:00,546 --> 00:45:05,633
or a trail, or the road,
so he'd tell us to get down, shut up...

568
00:45:05,718 --> 00:45:07,719
Get down! Shut up!

569
00:45:08,679 --> 00:45:10,138
...so we did.

570
00:45:27,698 --> 00:45:29,866
Now, I don't know much about anything,

571
00:45:29,950 --> 00:45:33,786
but I think some of America's
best young men served in this war.

572
00:45:33,871 --> 00:45:36,581
There was Dallas, from Phoenix,

573
00:45:38,292 --> 00:45:41,085
Cleveland, he was from Detroit.

574
00:45:41,211 --> 00:45:43,588
Hey, Tex. Hey, Tex.

575
00:45:43,714 --> 00:45:45,882
Man, what the hell's going on?

576
00:45:45,966 --> 00:45:50,303
And Tex was... Well, I don't remember
where Tex come from.

577
00:45:50,387 --> 00:45:51,929
Nothing.

578
00:45:56,060 --> 00:45:58,561
Fourth Platoon, on your feet.

579
00:45:58,646 --> 00:46:02,357
Still got 10 klicks to go to that river.
Move out.

580
00:46:02,441 --> 00:46:04,233
Come on, move out.

581
00:46:06,278 --> 00:46:08,696
Step it up. Look alive out there.

582
00:46:08,781 --> 00:46:13,117
The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always some place to go.

583
00:46:13,243 --> 00:46:14,619
Fire in the hole!

584
00:46:18,082 --> 00:46:20,416
Gump, check out that hole.

585
00:46:20,501 --> 00:46:23,502
And there was always something to do.

586
00:46:23,586 --> 00:46:26,755
- Mount them up.
- Spread out! Cover his back.

587
00:46:31,803 --> 00:46:37,432
One day, it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.

588
00:46:38,434 --> 00:46:41,311
We'd been through
every kind of rain there is:

589
00:46:41,437 --> 00:46:43,980
Little bitty stinging rain,

590
00:46:44,691 --> 00:46:47,359
and big old fat rain,

591
00:46:47,819 --> 00:46:50,529
rain that flew in sideways.

592
00:46:50,613 --> 00:46:54,658
And sometimes, rain even seemed
to come straight up from underneath.

593
00:46:56,452 --> 00:46:58,829
Shoot, it even rained at night.

594
00:46:59,872 --> 00:47:02,332
- Hey, Forrest.
- Hey, Bubba.

595
00:47:02,458 --> 00:47:05,752
I'm gonna lean up against you.
You just lean right back against me.

596
00:47:05,837 --> 00:47:09,673
This way, we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

597
00:47:10,633 --> 00:47:14,094
You know why we a good partnership,
Forrest?

598
00:47:14,178 --> 00:47:16,680
'Cause we be watching out
for one another,

599
00:47:16,806 --> 00:47:18,682
like brothers and stuff.

600
00:47:20,643 --> 00:47:24,312
Hey, Forrest, there's something
I've been thinking about.

601
00:47:24,397 --> 00:47:27,399
I got a very important question
to ask you.

602
00:47:29,026 --> 00:47:32,988
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

603
00:47:34,157 --> 00:47:35,782
Okay.

604
00:47:35,867 --> 00:47:39,327
Man, I tell you what,
I got it all figured out, too.

605
00:47:39,412 --> 00:47:42,205
So many pounds of shrimp
to pay off the boat,

606
00:47:42,331 --> 00:47:45,625
so many pounds for gas,
we can just live right on the boat.

607
00:47:45,710 --> 00:47:48,003
We ain't got to pay no rent.

608
00:47:48,087 --> 00:47:50,172
I'll be the captain,
we can just work it together,

609
00:47:50,256 --> 00:47:54,509
split everything right down the middle.
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50.

610
00:47:54,594 --> 00:47:58,180
And, hey, Forrest,
all the shrimp you can eat.

611
00:47:59,724 --> 00:48:01,516
That's a fine idea.

612
00:48:02,602 --> 00:48:04,728
Bubba did have a fine idea.

613
00:48:08,524 --> 00:48:11,610
I even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.

614
00:48:12,403 --> 00:48:15,614
I sent her letters,
not every day, but almost.

615
00:48:15,698 --> 00:48:20,702
I told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,

616
00:48:20,787 --> 00:48:23,538
and told her
how I thought about her always,

617
00:48:24,874 --> 00:48:27,834
and how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her

618
00:48:27,919 --> 00:48:30,420
just as soon as she had the time.

619
00:48:32,298 --> 00:48:34,800
I'd always let her know that I was okay.

620
00:48:36,093 --> 00:48:41,264
Then, I'd sign each letter,
"Love, Forrest Gump."

621
00:48:56,112 --> 00:48:59,865
This one day, we was out walking,
like always,

622
00:48:59,950 --> 00:49:02,910
and then, just like that,

623
00:49:03,829 --> 00:49:07,248
somebody turned off the rain
and the sun come out.

624
00:49:10,252 --> 00:49:12,086
Ambush!

625
00:49:12,587 --> 00:49:13,963
Take cover!

626
00:49:17,592 --> 00:49:18,759
Get down!

627
00:49:18,844 --> 00:49:20,302
Get the sixty!

628
00:49:23,473 --> 00:49:25,558
Get that pig up here, God damn it!

629
00:49:25,642 --> 00:49:27,768
Forrest, you okay?

630
00:49:30,981 --> 00:49:33,607
Strongarm! Strongarm!
Be advised, Strongarm!

631
00:49:34,150 --> 00:49:36,569
Medic, we got a man down!

632
00:49:36,653 --> 00:49:39,613
Strongarm, this is Leg Lima 6, over!

633
00:49:40,323 --> 00:49:43,659
Roger, Strongarm, be advised
we have incoming from the tree line

634
00:49:43,785 --> 00:49:47,288
at points blue plus two.
AKs and rockets...

635
00:49:47,956 --> 00:49:49,748
Misfire! Misfire!

636
00:49:52,127 --> 00:49:54,128
God damn it! Mac!

637
00:49:55,088 --> 00:49:58,507
Get that thing...
Fuck it, get it in the tree line!

638
00:49:59,467 --> 00:50:00,634
Jesus!

639
00:50:00,760 --> 00:50:02,970
My unit is down hard and hurting!

640
00:50:03,096 --> 00:50:06,640
Six are pulling back to Blue Line,
Leg Lima 6 out.

641
00:50:07,434 --> 00:50:09,393
Pull back! Pull back!

642
00:50:09,477 --> 00:50:11,604
Run! Run, Forrest!

643
00:50:11,688 --> 00:50:14,023
- Pull back!
- Forrest, Forrest!

644
00:50:14,149 --> 00:50:16,734
Run, man! Run!

645
00:50:16,818 --> 00:50:18,611
Pull back! Run!

646
00:50:20,447 --> 00:50:22,656
Run, God damn it, run!

647
00:50:43,845 --> 00:50:48,474
Medic! Can I get a medic?

648
00:50:48,850 --> 00:50:52,186
I ran and ran, just like Jenny told me to.

649
00:50:55,565 --> 00:50:59,777
I ran so far and so fast
that pretty soon I was all by myself,

650
00:50:59,861 --> 00:51:01,820
which was a bad thing.

651
00:51:02,364 --> 00:51:03,906
Bubba!

652
00:51:06,034 --> 00:51:09,828
Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure that he was okay.

653
00:51:13,541 --> 00:51:15,584
Any friendlies out there?

654
00:51:16,544 --> 00:51:18,711
Yeah, I've got three over here.

655
00:51:19,338 --> 00:51:21,339
Where the hell are you?

656
00:51:21,924 --> 00:51:23,257
Bubba?

657
00:51:24,343 --> 00:51:27,053
And on my way back to find Bubba,

658
00:51:27,179 --> 00:51:29,973
well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.

659
00:51:30,057 --> 00:51:31,265
Tex!

660
00:51:33,352 --> 00:51:34,352
Okay.

661
00:51:34,436 --> 00:51:38,398
I couldn't just let him lay there all alone,
scared the way he was,

662
00:51:38,524 --> 00:51:42,402
so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.

663
00:51:57,543 --> 00:51:59,961
And every time I went back
looking for Bubba,

664
00:52:00,087 --> 00:52:03,589
somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest. Help me."

665
00:52:11,265 --> 00:52:13,141
Can't hear... Can't hear...

666
00:52:15,436 --> 00:52:16,728
No sweat, man. Just lay back.

667
00:52:16,812 --> 00:52:19,313
You'll be okay. You'll be okay.

668
00:52:21,316 --> 00:52:24,360
I started to get scared
that I might never find Bubba.

669
00:52:24,445 --> 00:52:25,695
...over.

670
00:52:25,779 --> 00:52:29,073
Roger, Strongarm,
I know my position is danger close.

671
00:52:29,158 --> 00:52:30,992
We got Charlie all over this area.

672
00:52:31,118 --> 00:52:33,411
I gotta have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

673
00:52:33,495 --> 00:52:36,873
- Six, Strongarm, we want...
- Lieutenant Dan, Coleman's dead!

674
00:52:36,957 --> 00:52:38,166
I know he's dead!

675
00:52:38,292 --> 00:52:41,127
My whole goddamn platoon
is wiped out!

676
00:52:41,253 --> 00:52:42,587
- Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6.
- God damn it!

677
00:52:42,671 --> 00:52:45,381
- Copy this transmission. Over.
- What are you doing?

678
00:52:45,466 --> 00:52:48,801
Just leave me here! Get away.
Just leave me here! Get out!

679
00:52:48,927 --> 00:52:51,220
Leg Lima 6, Strongarm.
How copy this? Over.

680
00:52:51,305 --> 00:52:53,931
God, I said leave me here, God damn it!

681
00:52:54,016 --> 00:52:57,185
Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6,
this is Strongarm, be advised

682
00:52:57,311 --> 00:52:59,270
your fast movers
are inbound at this time, over.

683
00:52:59,354 --> 00:53:02,774
Then, it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.

684
00:53:03,650 --> 00:53:05,318
Something bit me!

685
00:53:12,201 --> 00:53:14,327
You chink son of a bitch!

686
00:53:16,830 --> 00:53:18,831
I can't leave the platoon.

687
00:53:18,957 --> 00:53:23,878
I told you to leave me there, Gump.
Forget about me. Get yourself out!

688
00:53:24,004 --> 00:53:26,130
Did you hear what I said?

689
00:53:26,840 --> 00:53:28,800
God damn it, put me down!

690
00:53:29,510 --> 00:53:31,552
Get your ass out of here!

691
00:53:34,848 --> 00:53:37,433
I didn't ask you to pull me out of there,
God damn you!

692
00:53:37,518 --> 00:53:38,851
Where the hell
do you think you're going?

693
00:53:38,977 --> 00:53:40,061
To get Bubba.

694
00:53:40,187 --> 00:53:44,023
I got an air strike inbound right now.
They're gonna nape the whole area.

695
00:53:44,149 --> 00:53:46,525
Gump, you stay here, God damn it!
That's an order!

696
00:53:46,651 --> 00:53:49,069
I gotta find Bubba!

697
00:54:05,044 --> 00:54:06,503
Forrest.

698
00:54:14,262 --> 00:54:16,930
- Bubba.
- I'm okay, Forrest.

699
00:54:17,723 --> 00:54:19,391
I'm okay.

700
00:54:27,233 --> 00:54:29,067
Oh, Bubba, no...

701
00:54:29,193 --> 00:54:31,403
Nah, I'm gonna be all right.

702
00:54:39,579 --> 00:54:42,247
Come on. Come on. Come on.

703
00:54:47,253 --> 00:54:48,753
I'm okay, Forrest.

704
00:54:50,089 --> 00:54:52,924
I'm okay, man. I'm fine.

705
00:55:29,962 --> 00:55:33,089
Helo's inbound.
Top smoke, get it out there!

706
00:55:34,133 --> 00:55:38,637
If I'd a known this was gonna be the
last time me and Bubba was gonna talk,

707
00:55:38,763 --> 00:55:41,056
I'd of thought of something better to say.

708
00:55:41,140 --> 00:55:42,641
Hey, Bubba.

709
00:55:43,768 --> 00:55:45,143
Hey, Forrest.

710
00:55:47,480 --> 00:55:50,690
Forrest, why'd this happen?

711
00:55:52,026 --> 00:55:53,818
You got shot.

712
00:55:55,529 --> 00:55:59,699
Then Bubba said something
I won't ever forget.

713
00:56:00,493 --> 00:56:02,160
I wanna go home.

714
00:56:04,163 --> 00:56:06,206
Bubba was my best good friend.

715
00:56:07,166 --> 00:56:11,711
And even I know that ain't something
you can find just around the corner.

716
00:56:11,837 --> 00:56:14,922
Bubba was gonna be
a shrimping boat captain,

717
00:56:15,006 --> 00:56:18,968
but instead he died right there
by that river in Vietnam.

718
00:56:24,683 --> 00:56:26,976
That's all I have to say about that.

719
00:56:29,354 --> 00:56:31,522
It was a bullet, wasn't it?

720
00:56:33,858 --> 00:56:36,527
- A bullet?
- That jumped up and bit you.

721
00:56:38,905 --> 00:56:40,990
Oh, yes, sir.

722
00:56:41,074 --> 00:56:44,201
Bit me directly in the buttocks.

723
00:56:44,327 --> 00:56:49,581
They said it was a million-dollar wound,
but the Army must keep that money,

724
00:56:49,708 --> 00:56:53,544
'cause I still ain't seen a nickel
of that million dollars.

725
00:56:54,379 --> 00:56:57,881
The only good thing
about being wounded in the buttocks

726
00:56:58,008 --> 00:56:59,717
is the ice cream.

727
00:56:59,843 --> 00:57:02,428
They gave me all the ice cream
I could eat.

728
00:57:02,554 --> 00:57:03,846
And guess what?

729
00:57:03,930 --> 00:57:07,057
A good friend of mine
was in the bed right next door.

730
00:57:09,269 --> 00:57:12,354
Lieutenant Dan,
I got you some ice cream.

731
00:57:14,733 --> 00:57:16,900
Lieutenant Dan, ice cream.

732
00:57:28,621 --> 00:57:30,914
It's time for your bath, Lieutenant.

733
00:57:39,424 --> 00:57:40,758
Harper!

734
00:57:43,970 --> 00:57:46,430
Cooper, Larson,

735
00:57:48,641 --> 00:57:49,975
Webster,

736
00:57:51,394 --> 00:57:54,897
- Gump. Gump.
- I'm Forrest Gump.

737
00:57:58,443 --> 00:58:01,737
Kyle, Nichols,

