That's all these cripples,
down at the VA,

986
01:17:35,903 --> 01:17:38,321
that's all they ever talk about.

987
01:17:39,490 --> 01:17:42,450
Jesus this and Jesus that.

988
01:17:43,911 --> 01:17:46,204
Have I found Jesus?

989
01:17:46,830 --> 01:17:49,832
They even had a priest come
and talk to me.

990
01:17:50,709 --> 01:17:55,380
He said God is listening,
but I have to help myself.

991
01:17:56,757 --> 01:17:59,050
How if I accept Jesus into my heart,

992
01:18:00,052 --> 01:18:03,846
I'll get to walk beside him
in the kingdom of heaven.

993
01:18:03,931 --> 01:18:06,099
Did you hear what I said?

994
01:18:07,142 --> 01:18:11,145
Walk beside him
in the kingdom of heaven.

995
01:18:11,230 --> 01:18:14,190
Well, kiss my crippled ass.

996
01:18:14,275 --> 01:18:17,652
God is listening? What a crock of shit.

997
01:18:21,323 --> 01:18:23,949
I'm going to heaven, Lieutenant Dan.

998
01:18:25,868 --> 01:18:26,910
Oh?

999
01:18:31,749 --> 01:18:33,125
Well,

1000
01:18:36,087 --> 01:18:39,464
before you go, why don't you get
your ass down to the corner

1001
01:18:39,549 --> 01:18:42,050
- and get us another bottle of Ripple.
- Yes, sir.

1002
01:18:42,135 --> 01:18:47,264
We are at approximately 45th Street
in New York City at One Astor Plaza.

1003
01:18:47,348 --> 01:18:49,182
This is the site of the old Astor Hotel.

1004
01:18:49,267 --> 01:18:51,476
What the hell is in Bayou La Batre?

1005
01:18:51,561 --> 01:18:53,895
- Shrimping boats.
- Shrimping boats?

1006
01:18:53,980 --> 01:18:56,398
Who gives a shit
about shrimping boats?

1007
01:18:56,482 --> 01:18:57,941
I gotta buy me
one of them shrimping boats,

1008
01:18:58,026 --> 01:18:59,568
soon as I have some money.

1009
01:18:59,652 --> 01:19:02,487
I made me a promise to Bubba
in Vietnam

1010
01:19:02,572 --> 01:19:05,282
that as soon as the war was over,
we'd go in partners.

1011
01:19:05,366 --> 01:19:08,785
He'd be the captain of the
shrimping boat and I'd be his first mate.

1012
01:19:08,870 --> 01:19:12,331
But now that he's dead,
that means I gotta be the captain.

1013
01:19:12,415 --> 01:19:15,125
- A shrimp boat captain.
- Yes, sir.

1014
01:19:15,209 --> 01:19:17,961
A promise is a promise, Lieutenant Dan.

1015
01:19:19,464 --> 01:19:21,923
Now hear this!

1016
01:19:22,675 --> 01:19:26,511
Private Gump here
is gonna be a shrimp boat captain.

1017
01:19:27,263 --> 01:19:28,680
Well, I tell you what, Gilligan,

1018
01:19:28,765 --> 01:19:31,224
the day that you are
a shrimp boat captain,

1019
01:19:31,309 --> 01:19:34,853
- I will come and be your first mate.
- Okay.

1020
01:19:34,937 --> 01:19:39,274
If you're ever a shrimp boat captain,
that's the day I'm an astronaut.

1021
01:19:39,359 --> 01:19:42,361
Danny, what are
you complaining about?

1022
01:19:42,445 --> 01:19:45,030
- What are you doing, hon?
- Mr. Hot Wheels.

1023
01:19:45,114 --> 01:19:48,742
- Who's your friend?
- My name is Forrest, Forrest Gump.

1024
01:19:49,577 --> 01:19:53,789
This is Cunning Carla
and Long-Limbs Lenore.

1025
01:19:54,874 --> 01:19:58,085
So, where you been, baby cakes, huh?
Haven't seen you around lately.

1026
01:19:58,169 --> 01:19:59,628
You know, you should have
been here for Christmas,

1027
01:19:59,712 --> 01:20:01,046
'cause Tommy bought a round
on the house

1028
01:20:01,130 --> 01:20:02,631
and gave everybody a turkey sandwich.

1029
01:20:02,715 --> 01:20:05,759
Well, well, I had company.

1030
01:20:06,636 --> 01:20:10,305
Hey, hey! We was just there.
That's at Times Square.

1031
01:20:10,932 --> 01:20:15,060
Don't you just love New Year's?
You get to start all over.

1032
01:20:15,144 --> 01:20:18,438
- Hey, Lenore...
- Everybody gets a second chance.

1033
01:20:18,523 --> 01:20:21,066
It's funny,
but in the middle of all that fun,

1034
01:20:21,150 --> 01:20:23,443
I began to think about Jenny,

1035
01:20:24,362 --> 01:20:28,824
wondering how she was spending
her New Year's night out in California.

1036
01:20:51,430 --> 01:20:54,932
...eight, seven, six, five,

1037
01:20:55,058 --> 01:20:58,519
four, three, two, one!

1038
01:20:58,645 --> 01:21:01,313
Happy New Year!

1039
01:21:17,789 --> 01:21:20,499
Happy New Year, Lieutenant Dan!

1040
01:21:55,786 --> 01:21:59,455
What are you, stupid or something?
What's your problem?

1041
01:22:00,123 --> 01:22:01,540
What's his problem?

1042
01:22:01,625 --> 01:22:03,876
Did you lose your pecker in the war
or something?

1043
01:22:03,960 --> 01:22:06,003
What, is your friend stupid
or something?

1044
01:22:06,087 --> 01:22:07,171
What did you say?

1045
01:22:07,255 --> 01:22:08,672
I said, is your friend stupid
or something?

1046
01:22:08,757 --> 01:22:10,925
Hey! Don't call him stupid!

1047
01:22:11,009 --> 01:22:12,968
- Hey, don't you push her!
- You shut up!

1048
01:22:13,053 --> 01:22:15,095
- Don't you ever call him stupid!
- What's the matter, baby?

1049
01:22:15,180 --> 01:22:16,889
- Why are you so upset?
- Just get the hell out of here.

1050
01:22:16,973 --> 01:22:18,057
- Stupid damn...
- Get your goddamn clothes...

1051
01:22:18,141 --> 01:22:19,642
You belong in Ripley's Believe It Or Not!

1052
01:22:19,726 --> 01:22:21,602
- Get the hell out of here!
- You should be in a sideshow!

1053
01:22:21,686 --> 01:22:22,728
Go on! Get out of here!

1054
01:22:22,813 --> 01:22:24,104
Come on, Lenore.
We don't need this shit!

1055
01:22:24,189 --> 01:22:25,564
Get out of here!

1056
01:22:27,192 --> 01:22:29,735
- You retard.
- Loser. You freak.

1057
01:22:35,116 --> 01:22:36,325
No, no.

1058
01:23:01,476 --> 01:23:05,437
I'm sorry I ruined your
New Year's Eve party, Lieutenant Dan.

1059
01:23:06,022 --> 01:23:08,315
She tasted like cigarettes.

1060
01:23:24,498 --> 01:23:29,002
I guess Lieutenant Dan figured there's
some things you just can't change.

1061
01:23:29,086 --> 01:23:34,215
He didn't want to be called crippled,
just like I didn't want to be called stupid.

1062
01:23:39,722 --> 01:23:41,598
Happy New Year, Gump.

1063
01:23:46,395 --> 01:23:47,770
The US Ping-Pong team

1064
01:23:47,855 --> 01:23:50,148
met with President Nixon today
at an Oval Office ceremony...

1065
01:23:50,232 --> 01:23:52,984
And wouldn't you know it?
A few months later,

1066
01:23:53,068 --> 01:23:57,030
they invited me and the Ping-Pong team
to visit the White House.

1067
01:23:57,114 --> 01:23:59,365
So, I went, again.

1068
01:24:00,200 --> 01:24:03,661
And I met the President
of the United States, again.

1069
01:24:04,413 --> 01:24:07,373
Only, this time, they didn't get us rooms
in a real fancy hotel.

1070
01:24:07,458 --> 01:24:10,835
So, are you enjoying yourself
in our nation's capital, young man?

1071
01:24:10,920 --> 01:24:13,922
- Yes, sir.
- Well, where are you staying?

1072
01:24:14,006 --> 01:24:16,633
- It's called the Hotel Ebbott.
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

1073
01:24:16,717 --> 01:24:19,844
I know of a much nicer hotel.
It's brand-new, very modern.

1074
01:24:19,929 --> 01:24:21,930
I'll have my people
take care of it for you.

1075
01:24:22,556 --> 01:24:23,681
Security, Frank Wills.

1076
01:24:23,766 --> 01:24:27,352
Yeah, sir, you might want
to send a maintenance man

1077
01:24:27,436 --> 01:24:30,104
over to that office across the way.

1078
01:24:30,189 --> 01:24:33,066
The lights are off, and they must be
looking for a fuse box or something,

1079
01:24:33,150 --> 01:24:35,860
'cause them flashlights,
they're keeping me awake.

1080
01:24:35,945 --> 01:24:37,570
Okay, sir. I'll check it out.

1081
01:24:37,655 --> 01:24:39,364
- Thank you.
- No problem.

1082
01:24:39,448 --> 01:24:41,366
- Good night.
- Good night.

1083
01:24:44,995 --> 01:24:50,375
Therefore, I shall resign the presidency
effective at noon tomorrow.

1084
01:24:50,459 --> 01:24:52,502
Vice President Ford

1085
01:24:52,586 --> 01:24:57,090
will be sworn in as president
at that hour in this office.

1086
01:24:58,467 --> 01:25:03,262
As I recall the high hopes for America
with which we began this second term...

1087
01:25:08,519 --> 01:25:10,061
Sergeant Gump.

1088
01:25:10,562 --> 01:25:12,772
- Yes, sir!
- As you were.

1089
01:25:12,856 --> 01:25:15,984
I have your discharge papers.
Your service is up, son.

1090
01:25:19,405 --> 01:25:22,156
Does this mean
I can't play Ping-Pong no more?

1091
01:25:22,241 --> 01:25:24,200
For the Army it does.

1092
01:25:26,829 --> 01:25:31,708
And just like that, my service
in the United States Army was over.

1093
01:25:37,006 --> 01:25:38,798
So, I went home.

1094
01:26:00,278 --> 01:26:03,697
- I'm home, Mama.
- I know, I know.

1095
01:26:05,324 --> 01:26:06,867
- Louise, he's here.
- Now, when I got home,

1096
01:26:06,951 --> 01:26:10,996
I had no idea,
but Mama had had all sorts of visitors.

1097
01:26:11,122 --> 01:26:13,415
We've had all sorts of visitors, Forrest.

1098
01:26:13,499 --> 01:26:16,585
Everybody wants you
to use their Ping-Pong stuff.

1099
01:26:16,669 --> 01:26:20,464
One man even left a check for $25,000

1100
01:26:20,548 --> 01:26:24,009
if you'd be agreeable to saying
you liked using their paddle.

1101
01:26:24,135 --> 01:26:26,803
Oh, but, Mama,
I only like using my own paddle.

1102
01:26:26,888 --> 01:26:28,889
- Hi, Miss Louise.
- Hey, Forrest.

1103
01:26:28,973 --> 01:26:31,892
I know that. I know that.

1104
01:26:31,976 --> 01:26:34,644
But it's $25,000, Forrest.

1105
01:26:34,729 --> 01:26:39,399
I thought maybe you could hold it
for a while, see if it grows on you.

1106
01:26:39,484 --> 01:26:41,610
- Oh, you look good, Forrest.
- That Mama, she sure was right.

1107
01:26:41,694 --> 01:26:44,196
- You look real good.
- It's funny how things work out.

1108
01:26:44,322 --> 01:26:47,449
I didn't stay home for long,
because I'd made a promise to Bubba,

1109
01:26:47,533 --> 01:26:49,785
and I always try to keep my promise.

1110
01:26:49,869 --> 01:26:51,411
So, I went on down to Bayou La Batre

1111
01:26:51,496 --> 01:26:55,248
to meet Bubba's family
and make their introduction.

1112
01:26:55,333 --> 01:26:59,002
Are you crazy, or just plain stupid?

1113
01:26:59,712 --> 01:27:01,963
Stupid is as stupid does, Mrs. Blue.

1114
01:27:02,048 --> 01:27:03,423
I guess.

1115
01:27:04,425 --> 01:27:08,011
And, of course,
I paid my respect to Bubba himself.

1116
01:27:10,014 --> 01:27:12,557
Hey, Bubba, it's me, Forrest Gump.

1117
01:27:15,686 --> 01:27:19,731
I remember everything you said,
and I got it all figured out.

1118
01:27:22,527 --> 01:27:29,324
I'm taking the $24,562
and 47 cents that I got...

1119
01:27:30,409 --> 01:27:33,995
Or, that's left after a new hair cut
and a new suit,

1120
01:27:34,080 --> 01:27:36,039
and I took Mama out
to a real fancy dinner,

1121
01:27:36,124 --> 01:27:39,376
and I bought a bus ticket
and three Dr. Peppers.

1122
01:27:39,919 --> 01:27:41,711
Tell me something.

1123
01:27:42,755 --> 01:27:44,881
Are you stupid or something?

1124
01:27:44,966 --> 01:27:47,008
Stupid is as stupid does, sir.

1125
01:27:47,093 --> 01:27:50,053
Well, that's what's left after me saying,

1126
01:27:50,972 --> 01:27:53,098
"When I was in China
on the All-America Ping-Pong team,

1127
01:27:53,224 --> 01:27:57,018
"I just loved playing Ping-Pong with
my Flex-O-Light Ping-Pong paddle,"

1128
01:27:57,103 --> 01:27:58,353
which everybody knows isn't true,

1129
01:27:58,437 --> 01:27:59,813
but Mama says it's just a little white lie

1130
01:27:59,897 --> 01:28:02,065
so it wouldn't hurt nobody.

1131
01:28:03,484 --> 01:28:09,406
So, anyway, I'm putting all that on gas,
ropes and new nets

1132
01:28:10,158 --> 01:28:11,908
and a brand-new shrimping boat.

1133
01:28:33,597 --> 01:28:36,849
Now, Bubba had told me everything
he knew about shrimping,

1134
01:28:36,933 --> 01:28:39,268
but you know what I found out?

1135
01:28:40,937 --> 01:28:43,272
Shrimping is tough.

1136
01:28:45,483 --> 01:28:47,318
I only caught five.

1137
01:28:47,444 --> 01:28:50,779
A couple more,
you could have yourself a cocktail.

1138
01:28:54,117 --> 01:28:55,868
Hey, you ever think
about naming this old boat?

1139
01:28:55,952 --> 01:28:58,621
It's bad luck
to have a boat without a name.

1140
01:29:00,999 --> 01:29:05,836
I'd never named a boat before,
but there was only one I could think of,

1141
01:29:07,005 --> 01:29:10,216
the most beautiful name
in the wide world.

1142
01:29:31,238 --> 01:29:34,073
Now, I hadn't heard from Jenny
in a long while,

1143
01:29:34,157 --> 01:29:36,700
but I thought about her a lot,

1144
01:29:36,826 --> 01:29:40,287
and I hoped that whatever
she was doing made her happy.

1145
01:31:26,560 --> 01:31:29,103
I thought about Jenny all the time.

1146
01:31:53,754 --> 01:31:54,921
Hey!

1147
01:32:18,779 --> 01:32:23,449
Lieutenant Dan,
what are you doing here?

1148
01:32:23,534 --> 01:32:27,453
Well, thought I'd try out my sea legs.

1149
01:32:27,538 --> 01:32:31,290
But you ain't got no legs,
Lieutenant Dan.

1150
01:32:31,375 --> 01:32:33,668
Yes, I know that.

1151
01:32:34,002 --> 01:32:36,045
You wrote me a letter, you idiot.

1152
01:32:36,171 --> 01:32:40,716
Well, well. Captain Forrest Gump.
I had to see this for myself.

1153
01:32:42,344 --> 01:32:49,225
And I told you if you were ever
a shrimp boat captain

1154
01:32:49,351 --> 01:32:51,936
that I'd be your first mate.
Well, here I am.

1155
01:32:52,020 --> 01:32:55,148
- I am a man of my word.
- Okay.

1156
01:32:55,232 --> 01:32:59,235
Yeah, but don't you be thinking that
I'm going to be calling you "sir."

1157
01:32:59,361 --> 01:33:00,695
No, sir.

1158
01:33:09,580 --> 01:33:11,872
That's my boat.

1159
01:33:14,459 --> 01:33:19,921
I have a feeling if we head due east,
we'll find some shrimp,

1160
01:33:20,047 --> 01:33:21,631
so take a left.

1161
01:33:23,050 --> 01:33:25,969
- Take a left!
- Which way?

1162
01:33:26,053 --> 01:33:28,722
Over there! They're over there!

1163
01:33:29,390 --> 01:33:33,226
- Get on the wheel and take a left!
- Okay.

1164
01:33:34,437 --> 01:33:38,565
Gump, what are you doing?
Take a left! Left!

1165
01:33:40,943 --> 01:33:44,571
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

1166
01:33:46,157 --> 01:33:47,741
That's where we'll find them.

1167
01:34:00,421 --> 01:34:04,549
- Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.
- Okay, so I was wrong.

1168
01:34:05,259 --> 01:34:08,470
How are we going to find them?

1169
01:34:08,596 --> 01:34:11,097
Well, maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

1170
01:34:17,730 --> 01:34:20,398
So, I went to church every Sunday.

1171
01:34:21,651 --> 01:34:23,652
Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came, too,

1172
01:34:23,778 --> 01:34:26,780
though I think
he left the praying up to me.

1173
01:34:42,255 --> 01:34:46,633
- No shrimp.
- Where the hell's this God of yours?

1174
01:34:47,468 --> 01:34:53,181
It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that,
'cause right then, God showed up.

1175
01:35:10,032 --> 01:35:14,869
- You'll never sink this boat!
- Now, me, I was scared,

1176
01:35:14,996 --> 01:35:18,039
but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.

1177
01:35:18,165 --> 01:35:19,499
Come on!

1178
01:35:22,628 --> 01:35:27,841
You call this a storm?
Come on, you son of a bitch!

1179
01:35:29,969 --> 01:35:34,347
It's time for a showdown! You and me!

1180
01:35:34,473 --> 01:35:38,351
I'm right here! Come and get me!

1181
01:35:40,145 --> 01:35:44,023
You'll never sink this boat!

1182
01:35:46,067 --> 01:35:48,235
Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,

1183
01:35:48,361 --> 01:35:50,904
destroying nearly everything in its path.

1184
01:35:51,031 --> 01:35:53,532
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

1185
01:35:53,700 --> 01:35:56,076
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

1186
01:35:56,161 --> 01:36:00,039
has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.

1187
01:36:00,165 --> 01:36:03,292
Speaking with local officials,
this reporter has learned,

1188
01:36:03,376 --> 01:36:06,837
in fact, only one shrimping boat
actually survived the storm.

1189
01:36:07,213 --> 01:36:09,840
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

1190
01:36:10,550 --> 01:36:12,551
After that, shrimping was easy.

1191
01:36:18,224 --> 01:36:21,352
Since people still needed
them shrimps for shrimp cocktails

1192
01:36:21,436 --> 01:36:25,564
and barbecues and all,
and we were the only boat left standing,

1193
01:36:25,732 --> 01:36:28,984
Bubba-Gump Shrimp's what they got.

1194
01:36:29,069 --> 01:36:33,656
We got a whole bunch of boats,
12 Jennys,

1195
01:36:33,740 --> 01:36:37,242
a big old warehouse. We even have
hats that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

1196
01:36:37,577 --> 01:36:40,871
Bubba-Gump Shrimp.
It's a household name.

1197
01:36:41,081 --> 01:36:42,790
Hold on there, boy.

1198
01:36:42,916 --> 01:36:47,461
Are you telling me you're the owner of
the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

1199
01:36:47,587 --> 01:36:50,589
Yes, sir. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

1200
01:36:52,217 --> 01:36:56,261
Boy, I heard some whoppers in my time,
but that tops them all.

1201
01:36:58,973 --> 01:37:01,767
We was sitting next to a millionaire.

1202
01:37:05,271 --> 01:37:09,900
Well, I thought it was a very lovely story,

1203
01:37:10,318 --> 01:37:14,947
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

1204
01:37:16,658 --> 01:37:19,326
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

1205
01:37:19,452 --> 01:37:20,953
Well, yes, I would.

1206
01:37:26,167 --> 01:37:28,210
That's him right there.

1207
01:37:30,338 --> 01:37:32,589
And let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan...

1208
01:37:33,758 --> 01:37:34,800
Forrest,

1209
01:37:40,348 --> 01:37:43,142
I never thanked you for saving my life.

1210
01:38:09,168 --> 01:38:15,465
He never actually said so,
but I think he made his peace with God.

1211
01:38:23,140 --> 01:38:25,349
For the second time in 17 days,

1212
01:38:25,476 --> 01:38:28,936
President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.

1213
01:38:29,021 --> 01:38:30,313
Base to Jenny 1.

1214
01:38:30,397 --> 01:38:33,900
- Base to Jenny 1.
- Jenny 1. Go, Margo.

1215
01:38:33,984 --> 01:38:35,485
Forrest has a phone call.

1216
01:38:35,569 --> 01:38:38,070
Yeah, well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

1217
01:38:38,155 --> 01:38:41,532
- He is indisposed at the moment.
- His mama's sick.

1218
01:39:02,221 --> 01:39:04,597
- Where's Mama?
- She's upstairs.

1219
01:39:07,434 --> 01:39:09,393
Hi, Forrest.

1220
01:39:10,354 --> 01:39:12,897
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- All right.

1221
01:39:19,571 --> 01:39:22,740
We sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

1222
01:39:34,086 --> 01:39:38,047
- What's the matter, Mama?
- I'm dying, Forrest.

1223
01:39:41,385 --> 01:39:43,761
Come on in, sit down over here.

1224
01:39:58,110 --> 01:40:01,612
- Why are you dying, Mama?
- It's my time.

1225
01:40:02,614 --> 01:40:04,490
It's just my time.

1226
01:40:05,951 --> 01:40:10,121
Now, don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

1227
01:40:11,748 --> 01:40:14,125
Death is just a part of life,

1228
01:40:15,127 --> 01:40:17,753
something we're all destined to do.

1229
01:40:19,590 --> 01:40:23,968
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

1230
01:40:24,803 --> 01:40:28,389
- I did the best I could.
- You did good, Mama.

1231
01:40:29,182 --> 01:40:34,352
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

1232
01:40:35,855 --> 01:40:39,107
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

1233
01:40:42,987 --> 01:40:45,113
What's my destiny, Mama?

1234
01:40:47,283 --> 01:40:50,493
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1235
01:40:51,787 --> 01:40:54,748
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1236
01:40:54,832 --> 01:40:57,000
You never know
what you're going to get.

1237
01:40:57,126 --> 01:41:01,504
Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.

1238
01:41:01,589 --> 01:41:03,798
I will miss you, Forrest.

1239
01:41:05,635 --> 01:41:09,679
She had got the cancer
and died on a Tuesday.

1240
01:41:11,182 --> 01:41:14,517
I bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.

1241
01:41:17,563 --> 01:41:20,857
And that's all I have to say about that.

1242
01:41:27,698 --> 01:41:29,991
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1243
01:41:30,076 --> 01:41:32,869
There'll be another one along shortly.

1244
01:41:36,707 --> 01:41:40,293
Now, because I had been a football star,
and a war hero,

1245
01:41:40,378 --> 01:41:43,505
and a national celebrity,
and a shrimping boat captain,

1246
01:41:44,006 --> 01:41:47,217
and a college graduate,
the city fathers of Greenbow, Alabama

1247
01:41:47,343 --> 01:41:50,553
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1248
01:41:51,931 --> 01:41:55,600
So, I never went back to work
for Lieutenant Dan,

1249
01:41:55,726 --> 01:41:58,436
though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.

1250
01:41:58,562 --> 01:42:03,149
He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.

1251
01:42:03,234 --> 01:42:04,818
And so then, I got a call from him saying

1252
01:42:04,902 --> 01:42:08,363
we don't have to worry about money
no more, and I said,

1253
01:42:08,447 --> 01:42:10,740
"That's good. One less thing."

1254
01:42:13,786 --> 01:42:17,163
Now, Mama said there's only
so much fortune a man really needs,

1255
01:42:18,416 --> 01:42:21,292
and the rest is just for showing off.

1256
01:42:21,377 --> 01:42:25,255
So, I gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare gospel church,

1257
01:42:27,925 --> 01:42:32,429
and I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.

1258
01:42:34,765 --> 01:42:39,310
And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,

1259
01:42:39,437 --> 01:42:42,063
I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.

1260
01:42:46,277 --> 01:42:47,986
You know what?

1261
01:42:49,238 --> 01:42:52,240
She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.

1262
01:42:52,324 --> 01:42:53,950
That smells wonderful.

1263
01:42:54,785 --> 01:42:58,705
And 'cause I was a gazillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,

1264
01:42:58,789 --> 01:43:01,124
I cut that grass for free.

1265
01:43:04,919 --> 01:43:07,796
But at night time
when there was nothing to do

1266
01:43:07,881 --> 01:43:10,257
and the house was all empty,

1267
01:43:11,259 --> 01:43:13,635
I'd always think of Jenny.

1268
01:44:17,325 --> 01:44:20,494
And then, she was there.

1269
01:44:53,486 --> 01:44:56,655
- Hello, Forrest.
- Hello, Jenny.

1270
01:45:08,209 --> 01:45:10,836
Jenny came back and stayed with me.

1271
01:45:12,422 --> 01:45:16,091
Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,

1272
01:45:16,217 --> 01:45:19,928
or maybe it was because she was
so tired, 'cause she went to bed

1273
01:45:20,054 --> 01:45:24,016
and slept and slept,
like she hadn't slept in years.

1274
01:45:25,268 --> 01:45:27,561
It was wonderful having her home.

1275
01:45:28,897 --> 01:45:34,025
Every day we'd take a walk and
I'd jabber on like a monkey in a tree,

1276
01:45:34,109 --> 01:45:36,652
and she'd listen about Ping-Ponging,
and shrimping,

1277
01:45:36,737 --> 01:45:41,032
and Mama making a trip up to heaven.
I did all the talking.

1278
01:45:41,116 --> 01:45:44,452
Jenny most of the time was real quiet.

1279
01:46:24,618 --> 01:46:27,828
How could you do this?

1280
01:47:04,783 --> 01:47:08,119
Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.

1281
01:47:10,330 --> 01:47:14,834
I never really knew why she came back,
but I didn't care.

1282
01:47:15,002 --> 01:47:19,297
It was like olden times.
We was like peas and carrots again.

1283
01:47:21,383 --> 01:47:25,720
Every day, I'd pick pretty flowers
and put them in her room for her,

1284
01:47:27,222 --> 01:47:30,808
and she gave me the best gift anyone
could ever get in the wide world.

1285
01:47:30,892 --> 01:47:33,728
- New shoes.
- They make them just for running.

1286
01:47:38,734 --> 01:47:42,028
And she even showed me
how to dance.

1287
01:47:50,203 --> 01:47:54,415
And, well, we was like family,
Jenny and me.

1288
01:47:58,169 --> 01:48:01,087
And it was the happiest time in my life.

1289
01:48:20,733 --> 01:48:22,525
...and this Fourth is witnessing
one of the

1290
01:48:22,610 --> 01:48:25,612
largest fireworks displays
in the nation's...

1291
01:48:25,696 --> 01:48:28,615
- You done watching it?
...here in New York Harbor...

1292
01:48:28,741 --> 01:48:30,533
- I'm going to bed.
...with a spectacular display

1293
01:48:30,618 --> 01:48:33,661
of tall ships earlier.
The Statue of Liberty...

1294
01:48:40,711 --> 01:48:42,712
Will you marry me?

1295
01:48:47,635 --> 01:48:50,595
I'd make a good husband, Jenny.

1296
01:48:53,265 --> 01:48:55,308
You would, Forrest.

1297
01:48:57,144 --> 01:48:59,479
But you won't marry me.

1298
01:49:01,774 --> 01:49:03,983
You don't want to marry me.

1299
01:49:07,571 --> 01:49:09,989
Why don't you love me, Jenny?

1300
01:49:14,995 --> 01:49:17,122
I'm not a smart man,

1301
01:49:18,833 --> 01:49:21,251
but I know what love is.

1302
01:49:58,289 --> 01:49:59,539
Jenny.

1303
01:50:01,459 --> 01:50:03,960
Forrest, I do love you.

1304
01:50:57,096 --> 01:51:00,766
- Where are you running off to?
- I'm not running.

1305
01:52:32,358 --> 01:52:37,696
That day, for no particular reason,
I decided to go for a little run.

1306
01:52:38,865 --> 01:52:43,285
So, I ran to the end of the road,
and when I got there,

1307
01:52:43,369 --> 01:52:45,120
I thought maybe I'd run
to the end of town.

1308
01:52:45,204 --> 01:52:48,457
President Carter, suffering from heat
exhaustion, fell into the arms of...

1309
01:52:48,541 --> 01:52:50,208
And when I got there,

1310
01:52:50,293 --> 01:52:54,462
I thought maybe I'd just
run across Greenbow County.

1311
01:52:54,546 --> 01:52:56,964
And I figured since I'd run this far,

1312
01:52:57,049 --> 01:53:00,301
maybe I'd just run across
the great state of Alabama.

1313
01:53:00,385 --> 01:53:01,594
And that's what I did.

1314
01:53:02,220 --> 01:53:04,013
I ran clear across Alabama.

1315
01:53:05,057 --> 01:53:08,225
For no particular reason,
I just kept on going.

1316
01:53:09,561 --> 01:53:11,145
I ran clear to the ocean.

1317
01:53:17,027 --> 01:53:20,196
And when I got there,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1318
01:53:20,739 --> 01:53:23,574
might as well turn around
and just keep on going.

1319
01:53:27,329 --> 01:53:31,916
And when I got to another ocean,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1320
01:53:33,710 --> 01:53:37,421
I might as well just turn back
and keep right on going.

1321
01:53:38,590 --> 01:53:43,427
When I got tired, I slept.
When I got hungry, I ate.

1322
01:53:43,512 --> 01:53:46,555
When I had to go, you know...

1323
01:53:48,183 --> 01:53:49,350
I went.

1324
01:53:49,434 --> 01:53:52,436
And so, you just ran.

1325
01:53:54,189 --> 01:53:55,272
Yeah.

1326
01:54:30,559 --> 01:54:35,813
I'd think a lot about Mama
and Bubba and Lieutenant Dan.

1327
01:54:36,815 --> 01:54:40,317
But most of all, I thought about Jenny.

1328
01:54:41,403 --> 01:54:43,571
I thought about her a lot.

1329
01:54:44,322 --> 01:54:47,408
For more than two years now,
a man named Forrest Gump,

1330
01:54:47,492 --> 01:54:50,911
a gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,
stopping only to sleep,

1331
01:54:50,996 --> 01:54:53,164
has been running across America.

1332
01:54:53,248 --> 01:54:55,249
Charles Cooper brings us this report.

1333
01:54:56,168 --> 01:54:58,586
For the fourth time
on his journey across America,

1334
01:54:58,670 --> 01:55:01,505
Forrest Gump,
the gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,

1335
01:55:01,631 --> 01:55:04,508
is about to cross
the Mississippi River again today.

1336
01:55:05,135 --> 01:55:07,178
- I'll be damned. Forrest?
- Sir, why are you running?

1337
01:55:07,262 --> 01:55:08,345
Why are you running?

1338
01:55:08,430 --> 01:55:10,014
Are you doing this for world peace?

1339
01:55:10,098 --> 01:55:11,432
Are you doing this for the homeless?

1340
01:55:11,516 --> 01:55:14,518
- Are you running for women's rights?
- Or for the environment?

1341
01:55:14,603 --> 01:55:15,603
Or for animals?

1342
01:55:15,687 --> 01:55:18,606
They just couldn't believe that
somebody would do all that running

1343
01:55:18,690 --> 01:55:20,065
for no particular reason.

1344
01:55:20,150 --> 01:55:22,108
Why are you doing this?

1345
01:55:22,193 --> 01:55:27,197
I just felt like running.

1346
01:55:27,323 --> 01:55:30,533
It's you. I can't believe it's really you.

1347
01:55:31,368 --> 01:55:36,498
Now, for some reason, what I was doing
seemed to make sense to people.

1348
01:55:36,665 --> 01:55:38,792
I mean, it was like an alarm
went off in my head, you know?

1349
01:55:38,876 --> 01:55:40,710
I said,
"Here's a guy that's got his act together.

1350
01:55:40,836 --> 01:55:42,796
"Here's somebody
who's got it all figured out.

1351
01:55:42,880 --> 01:55:46,966
"Here's somebody who has the answer."
I'll follow you anywhere, Mr. Gump.

1352
01:55:47,051 --> 01:55:48,885
So, I got company.

1353
01:55:50,721 --> 01:55:56,559
And after that, I got more company.
And then, even more people joined in.

1354
01:55:59,021 --> 01:56:02,232
Somebody later told me
it gave people hope.

1355
01:56:04,026 --> 01:56:07,403
Now... Now, I don't know
anything about that,

1356
01:56:08,239 --> 01:56:10,824
but some of those people
asked me if I could help them out.

1357
01:56:11,033 --> 01:56:14,285
Hey, man, hey, listen, I was wondering
if you might help me, huh?

1358
01:56:14,370 --> 01:56:16,120
Listen, I'm in the
bumper sticker business

1359
01:56:16,205 --> 01:56:17,956
and I've been trying
to think up a good slogan.

1360
01:56:18,040 --> 01:56:21,167
And since you have been such a big
inspiration to the people around here,

1361
01:56:21,252 --> 01:56:23,169
I thought you might
be able to help me jump into...

1362
01:56:23,254 --> 01:56:26,881
Whoa, man! You just ran through
a big pile of dog shit!

1363
01:56:28,425 --> 01:56:31,094
- It happens.
- What, shit?

1364
01:56:32,596 --> 01:56:34,556
Sometimes.

1365
01:56:36,433 --> 01:56:39,102
And some years later,
I heard that that fellow

1366
01:56:39,186 --> 01:56:40,812
did come up with
a bumper sticker slogan,

1367
01:56:40,896 --> 01:56:44,107
and he made a lot of money off of it.

1368
01:56:45,568 --> 01:56:47,777
Another time, I was running along,

1369
01:56:47,903 --> 01:56:51,197
somebody who had lost all his money
in the T-shirt business,

1370
01:56:51,282 --> 01:56:53,324
he wanted to put my face on a T-shirt,

1371
01:56:53,409 --> 01:56:56,369
but he couldn't draw that well,
and he didn't have a camera.

1372
01:56:56,453 --> 01:56:59,956
Here, use this one.
Nobody likes that color anyway.

1373
01:57:04,795 --> 01:57:06,462
Have a nice day.

1374
01:57:08,090 --> 01:57:09,215
Well, some years later,

1375
01:57:09,300 --> 01:57:13,219
I found out that that man
did come up with an idea for a T-shirt.

1376
01:57:13,304 --> 01:57:15,680
He made a lot of money off of it.

1377
01:57:18,475 --> 01:57:22,896
Anyway, like I was saying,
I had a lot of company.

1378
01:57:24,148 --> 01:57:25,315
My mama always said,

1379
01:57:25,399 --> 01:57:29,819
"You got to put the past behind you
before you can move on."

1380
01:57:31,488 --> 01:57:34,824
And I think that's what
my running was all about.

1381
01:57:35,659 --> 01:57:39,662
I had run for three years, two months,

1382
01:57:39,914 --> 01:57:42,248
14 days and 16 hours.

1383
01:57:57,931 --> 01:58:00,265
Quiet. Quiet.
He's going to say something.

1384
01:58:11,694 --> 01:58:13,445
I'm pretty tired.

1385
01:58:16,282 --> 01:58:18,325
Think I'll go home now.

1386
01:58:36,886 --> 01:58:39,346
Now what are we supposed to do?

1387
01:58:40,306 --> 01:58:44,559
And just like that,
my running days was over.

1388
01:58:46,521 --> 01:58:48,271
So, I went home to Alabama.

1389
01:58:49,065 --> 01:58:53,235
Moments ago, at 2:25 p.m.,
as President Reagan was leaving the...

1390
01:58:54,988 --> 01:58:59,157
...five or six gunshots were fired
by an unknown would-be assassin.

1391
01:58:59,659 --> 01:59:01,994
The President was shot in the chest,
and the assailant...

1392
01:59:02,078 --> 01:59:04,037
I picked up the mail.

1393
01:59:04,831 --> 01:59:08,667
And one day, out of the blue clear sky,
I got a letter from Jenny,

1394
01:59:08,751 --> 01:59:13,005
wondering if I could come down
to Savannah and see her,

1395
01:59:13,089 --> 01:59:15,674
and that's what I'm doing here.

1396
01:59:15,758 --> 01:59:18,343
She saw me on TV, running.

1397
01:59:18,428 --> 01:59:22,681
I'm supposed to go on the
number nine bus to Richmond Street

1398
01:59:22,765 --> 01:59:29,688
and get off and go one block left
to 1947 Henry Street, Apartment 4.

1399
01:59:29,772 --> 01:59:33,442
Why, you don't need to take a bus.

1400
01:59:33,568 --> 01:59:38,113
Henry Street is just five
or six blocks down that way.

1401
01:59:39,949 --> 01:59:42,284
- Down that way?
- Down that way.

1402
01:59:45,288 --> 01:59:47,205
It was nice talking to you.

1403
01:59:48,249 --> 01:59:50,876
I hope everything works out for you!

1404
01:59:58,634 --> 02:00:00,302
Hey!

1405
02:00:00,720 --> 02:00:02,387
Forrest!

1406
02:00:02,638 --> 02:00:05,891
How you doing? Come in, come in!

1407
02:00:05,975 --> 02:00:07,184
I got your letter.

1408
02:00:07,268 --> 02:00:09,895
I was wondering about that.

1409
02:00:11,439 --> 02:00:13,231
Is this your house?

1410
02:00:13,316 --> 02:00:16,401
Yeah. It's messy right now.
I just got off work.

1411
02:00:16,486 --> 02:00:20,196
It's nice. You got air conditioning.

1412
02:00:27,079 --> 02:00:29,121
- Thank you.
- I ate some.

1413
02:00:31,917 --> 02:00:37,338
Hey, I kept a scrapbook
of your clippings and everything.

1414
02:00:37,464 --> 02:00:39,090
There you are.

1415
02:00:40,842 --> 02:00:41,926
And this, I got you running.

1416
02:00:45,013 --> 02:00:47,181
I ran a long way,

1417
02:00:47,682 --> 02:00:49,517
for a long time.

1418
02:00:51,728 --> 02:00:53,229
And there...

1419
02:00:59,736 --> 02:01:03,197
Listen, Forrest,
I don't know how to say this.

1420
02:01:05,700 --> 02:01:10,037
I just I want to apologize
for anything that I ever did to you,

1421
02:01:10,163 --> 02:01:15,417
'cause I was messed up
for a long time, and...

1422
02:01:18,213 --> 02:01:19,839
- Hey.
- Hi.

1423
02:01:20,048 --> 02:01:21,048
Hey, you.

1424
02:01:22,217 --> 02:01:25,177
- This is an old friend from Alabama.
- How do you do?

1425
02:01:25,262 --> 02:01:28,347
Listen, next week my schedule changes,
so I'll be able to... But thanks...

1426
02:01:28,431 --> 02:01:30,474
No problem. Got to go, Jen,
I'm double-parked.

1427
02:01:30,559 --> 02:01:32,434
- Okay. Thanks.
- Bye.

1428
02:01:35,897 --> 02:01:38,649
This is my very good friend, Mr. Gump.
Can you say hi to him?

1429
02:01:38,733 --> 02:01:41,819
- Hello, Mr. Gump.
- Hello.

1430
02:01:41,903 --> 02:01:44,905
- Can I go watch TV now?
- Yes, you can. Just keep it low.

1431
02:01:47,742 --> 02:01:51,078
- You're a mama, Jenny.
- I'm a mama.

1432
02:01:53,957 --> 02:01:55,791
His name's Forrest.

1433
02:01:56,918 --> 02:01:58,252
Like me.

1434
02:01:59,880 --> 02:02:02,006
I named him after his daddy.

1435
02:02:02,966 --> 02:02:05,426
He got a daddy named Forrest, too?

1436
02:02:06,720 --> 02:02:08,762
You're his daddy, Forrest.

1437
02:02:23,236 --> 02:02:24,445
Hey.

1438
02:02:25,614 --> 02:02:28,490
Forrest, look at me.
Look at me, Forrest.

1439
02:02:31,077 --> 02:02:35,206
There's nothing you need to do, okay?
You didn't do anything wrong.

1440
02:02:35,749 --> 02:02:37,124
Okay?

1441
02:02:41,463 --> 02:02:43,339
Isn't he beautiful?

1442
02:02:44,341 --> 02:02:47,300
He's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1443
02:02:51,096 --> 02:02:52,180
But...

1444
02:02:55,851 --> 02:02:58,728
Is he smart, or...

1445
02:02:58,812 --> 02:03:02,815
He's very smart.
He's one of the smartest in his class.

1446
02:03:12,159 --> 02:03:14,619
Yeah, it's okay. Go talk to him.

1447
02:03:23,963 --> 02:03:26,798
- What are you watching?
- Bert and Ernie.

1448
02:03:49,905 --> 02:03:51,698
Forrest,

1449
02:03:53,158 --> 02:03:54,701
I'm sick.

1450
02:03:57,371 --> 02:04:00,999
What, do you have
a cough due to a cold?

1451
02:04:01,083 --> 02:04:03,459
I have some kind of virus,

1452
02:04:03,544 --> 02:04:06,254
and the doctors don't...
They don't know what it is,

1453
02:04:06,380 --> 02:04:09,382
and there isn't anything
they can do about it.

1454
02:04:13,762 --> 02:04:16,055
You could come home with me.

1455
02:04:17,725 --> 02:04:23,396
Jenny, you and little Forrest could
come stay at my house in Greenbow.

1456
02:04:27,735 --> 02:04:30,528
I'll take care of you if you're sick.

1457
02:04:32,906 --> 02:04:35,199
Would you marry me, Forrest?

1458
02:04:40,456 --> 02:04:41,706
Okay.

1459
02:04:42,750 --> 02:04:44,417
Please take your seats.

1460
02:04:48,255 --> 02:04:50,590
Forrest? It's time to start.

1461
02:05:09,985 --> 02:05:11,569
Hi.

1462
02:05:12,446 --> 02:05:13,945
Your tie.

1463
02:05:26,501 --> 02:05:45,435
Lieutenant Dan.

1464
02:05:46,270 --> 02:05:47,938
Hello, Forrest.

1465
02:05:48,606 --> 02:05:51,274
You got new legs. New legs!

1466
02:05:52,485 --> 02:05:56,279
Yeah. I got new legs. Custom-made.

1467
02:05:56,989 --> 02:06:00,992
Titanium alloy.
It's what they use on the space shuttle.

1468
02:06:04,831 --> 02:06:06,331
Magic legs.

1469
02:06:08,334 --> 02:06:12,712
This is my fiancÃ©e, Susan.

1470
02:06:15,508 --> 02:06:18,885
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hi, Forrest.

1471
02:06:20,972 --> 02:06:24,182
Lieutenant Dan, this is my Jenny.

1472
02:06:24,559 --> 02:06:27,561
Hey. It's nice to meet you finally.

1473
02:06:37,697 --> 02:06:41,867
Do you, Forrest,
take Jenny to be your wife?

1474
02:06:43,744 --> 02:06:47,998
Do you, Jenny,
take Forrest to be your husband?

1475
02:06:49,333 --> 02:06:52,711
And so I pronounce you man and wife.

1476
02:07:23,576 --> 02:07:25,452
- Hey.
- Hey.

1477
02:07:39,133 --> 02:07:40,925
Hey, Forrest.

1478
02:07:46,264 --> 02:07:48,057
Were you scared in Vietnam?

1479
02:07:49,726 --> 02:07:52,061
Yes. Well, I...

1480
02:07:53,396 --> 02:07:55,105
I don't know.

1481
02:07:55,815 --> 02:08:00,778
Sometimes it would stop raining long
enough for the stars to come out.

1482
02:08:03,907 --> 02:08:05,950
And then it was nice.

1483
02:08:09,329 --> 02:08:13,290
It was like just before the sun
goes to bed down on the bayou.

1484
02:08:14,584 --> 02:08:18,462
There was always
a million sparkles on the water.

1485
02:08:20,257 --> 02:08:24,176
Like that mountain lake.
It was so clear, Jenny,

1486
02:08:24,302 --> 02:08:28,889
it looked like there were two skies,
one on top of the other.

1487
02:08:31,434 --> 02:08:34,478
And then, in the desert,
when the sun comes up,

1488
02:08:36,940 --> 02:08:41,110
I couldn't tell where heaven stopped

1489
02:08:41,653 --> 02:08:44,029
and the earth began.

1490
02:08:45,282 --> 02:08:47,157
It was so beautiful.

1491
02:08:51,871 --> 02:08:54,957
I wish I could've been there with you.

1492
02:08:58,044 --> 02:08:59,461
You were.

1493
02:09:10,181 --> 02:09:11,640
I love you.

1494
02:09:16,021 --> 02:09:19,356
You died on a Saturday morning.

1495
02:09:21,067 --> 02:09:24,820
And I had you placed
here under our tree.

1496
02:09:29,701 --> 02:09:34,538
And I had that house of your father's
bulldozed to the ground.

1497
02:09:38,668 --> 02:09:40,336
Mama

1498
02:09:41,421 --> 02:09:46,425
always said that dying was a part of life.

1499
02:09:49,846 --> 02:09:52,181
I sure wish it wasn't.

1500
02:09:54,851 --> 02:09:58,604
Little Forrest is doing just fine.

1501
02:09:59,939 --> 02:10:01,023
But...

1502
02:10:01,274 --> 02:10:03,942
About to start school again soon,

1503
02:10:05,779 --> 02:10:09,572
and I make his breakfast, lunch
and dinner every day.

1504
02:10:11,742 --> 02:10:17,747
I make sure he combs his hair
and brushes his teeth every day.

1505
02:10:20,876 --> 02:10:23,461
Teaching him how to play Ping-Pong.

1506
02:10:24,755 --> 02:10:25,797
Okay.

1507
02:10:26,048 --> 02:10:27,215
He's really good.

1508
02:10:27,299 --> 02:10:29,425
Forrest, you go.

1509
02:10:33,639 --> 02:10:35,223
We fish a lot.

1510
02:10:38,769 --> 02:10:42,230
And every night, we read a book.
He's so smart, Jenny.

1511
02:10:45,484 --> 02:10:47,735
You'd be so proud of him.

1512
02:10:49,446 --> 02:10:50,905
I am.

1513
02:10:51,949 --> 02:10:55,159
He wrote you a letter.

1514
02:10:56,745 --> 02:10:58,788
And he says I can't read it.

1515
02:10:58,914 --> 02:11:02,458
I'm not supposed to,
so I'll just leave it here for you.

1516
02:11:18,517 --> 02:11:19,851
Jenny,

1517
02:11:25,649 --> 02:11:28,860
I don't know if Mama was right,

1518
02:11:30,195 --> 02:11:31,696
or if it's Lieutenant Dan.

1519
02:11:31,822 --> 02:11:34,407
I don't know

1520
02:11:34,491 --> 02:11:38,995
if we each have a destiny,

1521
02:11:41,039 --> 02:11:46,169
or if we're all just floating around
accidental-like on a breeze.

1522
02:11:50,674 --> 02:11:52,508
But I think

1523
02:11:54,386 --> 02:11:56,179
maybe it's both.

1524
02:12:00,517 --> 02:12:03,394
Maybe both is happening
at the same time.

1525
02:12:09,526 --> 02:12:11,527
But I miss you, Jenny.

1526
02:12:17,910 --> 02:12:22,330
If there's anything you need,
I won't be far away.

1527
02:12:57,615 --> 02:13:00,575
Here's your bus. Okay.

1528
02:13:02,245 --> 02:13:05,580
Hey. I know this.

1529
02:13:05,706 --> 02:13:08,583
I'm gonna show that
for show-and-tell because

1530
02:13:08,709 --> 02:13:11,378
Grandma used to read it to you.

1531
02:13:11,462 --> 02:13:13,588
My favorite book.

1532
02:13:16,926 --> 02:13:18,426
Here we are.

1533
02:13:18,594 --> 02:13:20,053
Okay.

1534
02:13:21,764 --> 02:13:23,265
Here you go.

1535
02:13:28,145 --> 02:13:30,647
Hey, Forrest, don't...

1536
02:13:34,110 --> 02:13:37,821
- I wanted to tell you, I love you.
- I love you, too, Daddy.

1537
02:13:39,824 --> 02:13:42,617
I'll be right here when you get back.

1538
02:13:47,164 --> 02:13:50,417
You understand this is
the bus to school, now, don't you?

1539
02:13:50,501 --> 02:13:54,045
Of course, and you are Dorothy Harris,
and I'm Forrest Gump.

